barplot example

months <-rep(c("jan", "feb", "mar", "apr", "may", "jun", 
               "jul", "aug", "sep", "oct", "nov", "dec"), 2)
chickens <-c(1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 4, 5, 4, 3, 4, 2, 2)
eggs <-c(0, 8, 10, 13, 16, 20, 25, 20, 18, 16, 10, 8)
values <-c(chickens, eggs)
type <-c(rep("chickens", 12), rep("eggs", 12))
mydata <-data.frame(months, values, type)
head(mydata)
##   months values     type
## 1    jan      1 chickens
## 2    feb      2 chickens
## 3    mar      3 chickens
## 4    apr      3 chickens
## 5    may      3 chickens
## 6    jun      4 chickens
library(ggplot2)

# p +geom_bar()

, ggplot2 x .

? factor .

factor levels .

mydata$months <-factor(mydata$months, 
                      levels = c("jan", "feb", "mar", "apr", "may", "jun", "jul", "aug", "sep", "oct", "nov", "dec"))

ggplot .

p <-ggplot(mydata, aes(months, values))
p +geom_bar(stat = "identity", aes(fill = type))

plot beside ?

p <-ggplot(mydata, aes(months, values))
p +geom_bar(stat = "identity", aes(fill = type), position="dodge")

text . label .

ggplot(mydata, aes(months, values))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", aes(fill = type), position="dodge") +
  geom_text(aes(label=values))

geom_text position_dodge(width) . vjust y .

ggplot(mydata, aes(x=months, y=values, fill=type))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity",  position="dodge") +
  geom_text(aes(label=values), position=position_dodge(width=1), vjust=-0.25)

.

values <-c(chickens, -eggs)
type <-c(rep("chickens", 12), rep("eggs", 12))
mydata <-data.frame(months, values, type)
mydata$months <-factor(mydata$months, 
                      levels = c("jan", "feb", "mar", "apr", "may", "jun", "jul", "aug", "sep", "oct", "nov", "dec"))

ggplot(mydata, aes(x=months, y=values, fill=type))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity",  position="identity") +
  geom_text(aes(label=values))+coord_flip()

pie chart example

ggplot() geom_bar() .

.

count.data <- data.frame(
  class = c("1st", "2nd", "3rd", "Crew"),
  n = c(325, 285, 706, 885),
  prop = c(14.8, 12.9, 32.1, 40.2)
)
count.data
##   class   n prop
## 1   1st 325 14.8
## 2   2nd 285 12.9
## 3   3rd 706 32.1
## 4  Crew 885 40.2
mycols <- c("#0073C2FF", "#EFC000FF", "#868686FF", "#CD534CFF")

p1<- ggplot(count.data, aes(x = "", y = prop, fill = class)) +
     geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity", color = "white") +
     coord_polar("y", start = 0)+
     scale_fill_manual(values = mycols) 
p1

p1+ geom_text(aes(label = prop), color = "white")

% label .

ggplot class count.data .

count.data geom_text .

library(dplyr)
## Warning: package 'dplyr' was built under R version 3.6.3
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
count.data <- count.data %>%
  arrange(desc(class)) %>%
  mutate(lab.ypos = cumsum(prop) - 0.5*prop)

p1+ geom_text(data=count.data, aes(label = prop,y = lab.ypos), color = "white")

xlim() .

ggplot(count.data, aes(x = 2, y = prop, fill = class)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", color = "white") +
  coord_polar(theta = "y", start = 0)+
  geom_text(aes(y = lab.ypos, label = prop), color = "white")+
  scale_fill_manual(values = mycols) +
  xlim(0.5, 2.5)

map example

library(maps)
## Warning: package 'maps' was built under R version 3.6.3
world_map <- map_data("world")
ggplot(world_map, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group)) +
  geom_polygon(fill="lightgray", colour = "white")

some.eu.countries <- c(
  "Portugal", "Spain", "France", "Switzerland", "Germany",
  "Austria", "Belgium", "UK", "Netherlands",
  "Denmark", "Poland", "Italy", 
  "Croatia", "Slovenia", "Hungary", "Slovakia",
  "Czech republic"
)
# Retrievethe map data
some.eu.maps <- map_data("world", region = some.eu.countries)

# Compute the centroid as the mean longitude and lattitude
# Used as label coordinate for country's names
region.lab.data <- some.eu.maps %>%
  group_by(region) %>%
  summarise(long = mean(long), lat = mean(lat))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
ggplot(some.eu.maps, aes(x = long, y = lat)) +
  geom_polygon(aes( group = group, fill = region))+
  geom_text(aes(label = region), data = region.lab.data,  size = 3, hjust = 0.5)

arrests <- USArrests 
arrests$region <- tolower(rownames(USArrests))
head(arrests)
##            Murder Assault UrbanPop Rape     region
## Alabama      13.2     236       58 21.2    alabama
## Alaska       10.0     263       48 44.5     alaska
## Arizona       8.1     294       80 31.0    arizona
## Arkansas      8.8     190       50 19.5   arkansas
## California    9.0     276       91 40.6 california
## Colorado      7.9     204       78 38.7   colorado
# Retrieve the states map data and merge with crime data
states_map <- map_data("state")
arrests_map <- merge(states_map, arrests, by = "region")

# Create the map
ggplot(arrests_map, aes(long, lat, group = group))+
  geom_polygon(aes(fill = Assault), color = "white")+
  scale_fill_gradient(low="blue", high="yellow")
